SIMPLE: inessential
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inessential
<hw>In`es*sen"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>essential</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inessentiel</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no essence or being.</def> <rj><au>H.
Brooke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The womb of <qex>inessential</qex> Naught.</q>
<rj><qau>Shelley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not essential; not required to achieve a given
purpose; unessential; unnecessary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inestimable</ent>⟦br⟧
